sub_title: Senior application specialist Epic/ ICT manager
summary:
Senior Epic application Specialist and ICT manager. Certifications from 2012 onwards: Ambulatory (outpatient), Cadence (scheduling), Kaleidoscope (ophthalmology), Cupid (cardiology), Bridges (interfaces) and Referrals & Authorizations. Not too bad at modules such as Optime (OR). Mainly responsible for Epic maintenance and optimizations. Examples of individual and team implementations 

2021-2022
- implemented Authorizations module at Plastic surgery department
- optimized cadence scheduling at Ophthalmology
- presented at XGM conference 

2020:
- implemented Authorizations module at Ophthalmology
- Building Care Paths, reporting workbench reports & Notewriter for sending data to the National Cataract registry
- Implemented Epics Dicom modality worklist & filing of HL7 measurements from modalities
- Dashboard-build for physicians & management
- Building Mychart questionnaires for various departments

2019
- Implemented waiting times on screens in outpatient clinic
- Optimizing outpatient scheduling at Ophthalmology

2018 and before:
- part of the implementation team of Cardiology - Cupid. General build for Cath lab and echocardiographies (including xml measurement import and Notewriter build)
- presented at EPIC XGM conference
- Consultancy / Go-live support at Dutch hospitals (OLVG, AmsterdamMC, UMCG, Amphia) and UCLH London
- implementation of Ambulatory and Kaleidoscope functionality at Ophthalmology

Also working as ICT manager at Ophthalmology. Mainly responsible for managing Dicom & PACS systems.
